<br>
To shop, simply type /bazaar. This will bring up a search screen to help you find what you want. You can search by race, class, slot, stat, item name, item type, etc. Note that containers currently cannot be sold this way, items being sold must be placed in a container. When you find something you want, you can right-click on the name of the seller, and you will be turned in the direction of his/her current location. Go that way, right-clicking periodically to correct until you find the seller. Perform the transaction the same way you would with an npc merchant.<br>
<br>
To sell, simply buy one or more Trader's Satchels from one of the merchants near the Nexus. Place the items you want to sell in the Satchel (I believe you are currently limited to 30 items). Go stand in one of the stalls, and type /trader. Then select each item you want to sell in the window, and enter the price you want to ask; &quot;Accept&quot; it, and press &quot;Set Price&quot;. This information will be saved in a text file in your Everquest directory, so that the next time you try to sell the same item, you will already have a default price. Once you have set all the prices, press &quot;Begin Trader&quot;, and your items will now be searcheable with the /bazaar command. Players can come to you, and purchase as if you were an npc. One extra suggestion would be to place an AFK message informing people that you are selling, and listing your current /loc (e.g. &quot;/afk Selling in the Bazaar at loc neg 993, neg 80. Happy Shopping!&quot;).<br>
<br>
Note that you continue to consume food and drink while in Trader mode. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kiroc>Kiroc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 233<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/21/02 4:40:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1797.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Bazaar Filters</span><hr size=1> If you're looking for something in particular (say a &quot;Jade Mace&quot;) you can type this into the Bazaar window (at the top) or look for partial matches.<br>
<br>
You can also (as previously mentioned) search by class, race, slot, etc.<br>
<br>
It's worth using more than 1 filter, as just searching for &quot;Monk&quot; items won't list every Monk item for sale - it seems to pick a random selection, so if you're looking for a Wu Mantle (for whatever reason <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) use either &quot;Wu&quot; as a search text or select &quot;Monk&quot; and &quot;Shoulder&quot; slot.<br>
